// Zellij config — shared across OSes via ~/.config/zellij.
// Stock keybindings: we deliberately use Zellij's DEFAULT preset (NO custom keybinds block) —
// prefix-free Alt+hjkl nav, modal Ctrl-p/t/n/s/o, Ctrl+g locked mode. tmux is mimicked only in
// WezTerm's leader for native pwsh panes, not here. TUI keys Zellij grabs (e.g. Claude Code's
// Alt+P) pass through via on-demand Ctrl+g locked mode.
// Design: docs/superpowers/specs/2026-06-25-zellij-stock-keybindings-design.md
//
// Modifier contract (Windows): Komorebi/AHK now lives entirely on the Hyper key
// (Ctrl+Alt+Shift+Win), so Alt is free for the terminal — Zellij's default Alt binds
// (Alt+n new pane, Alt+f floating, Alt+hjkl move-focus) are live again here. To pass an
// Alt key THROUGH to a TUI like Claude Code (e.g. Alt+P), toggle locked mode with Ctrl+g.
// See .config/komorebi/komorebi.ahk and
// docs/superpowers/specs/2026-06-25-komorebi-hyper-keybinds-design.md.

theme "catppuccin-frappe"

copy_on_select true
// copy_command "clip.exe"   // uncomment ONLY if Zellij's native clipboard copy fails on Windows

session_serialization true
serialize_pane_viewport true

scrollback_editor "nvim"

// Default shell for new panes/tabs — match the WezTerm setup (pwsh 7; see wezterm.lua:99-104,219).
// Windows-only today: this dir is NOT symlinked on macOS/Linux (deploy.sh / setup_mac.sh skip zellij),
// so a Windows path is safe here. If zellij is later adopted on mac/linux, guard this — those OSes
// want $SHELL/zsh, not a Windows pwsh path.
// NOTE: default_shell takes a PATH ONLY — it can't pass -NoLogo, so pwsh prints its 1-line startup
// banner per pane (cosmetic; pwsh 7.2+ trimmed it to a single line). The `agents` layout still passes
// -NoLogo. KNOWN LIMITATION (zellij#5052, verified 2026-06-25 on 0.44.3): a new ad-hoc pane opens in
// the session STARTUP dir, not the cd'd dir. Cause: zellij infers cwd by process-inspection, which
// fails for pwsh on Windows (same class as nushell #3068); it does NOT consume OSC-7 yet (#3512), so
// our prompt's OSC-7 emission can't help. Workaround: `cd` in the new pane, or pin `cwd` in a layout.
default_shell "C:\\Program Files\\PowerShell\\7\\pwsh.exe"

// layout_dir MUST be set explicitly on Windows for custom layouts (e.g. `agents`) to show up in the
// session-manager / layout-manager pickers. Those pickers enumerate the layout dir with Rust
// `read_dir`, which returns EMPTY when the path is reached through a Windows SYMLINK — and
// deploy_windows.ps1 symlinks ~/.config/zellij. (With no explicit layout_dir, Windows' default
// layout-dir resolution also comes back unusable.) Pointing layout_dir at the REAL repo dir (no
// reparse point) lets read_dir enumerate, so the pickers list custom layouts. Proven via
// `zellij action dump-screen`. The `zellij -n agents` CLI worked regardless — it opens the file by
// name, not via read_dir, which is why this was easy to miss.
// MACHINE-SPECIFIC path: KDL can't expand env vars or ~, so update this if the repo lives elsewhere.
// (Requires a Zellij server restart — `zellij ka`, then relaunch.)
layout_dir "C:\\Users\\mint\\dotfiles\\.config\\zellij\\layouts"
